investigation.title: Impact of Antiorthostatic Suspension on Mouse response to Tetanus Toxoid and CpG
investigation.description: These data were generated from mice that were skeletally unloaded using antiorthostatic suspension (AOS). Mice were either subjected to AOS or tail restraint without unloading for two weeks before injection with saline±tetanus toxoid±Cpg.

project.funding: This research is supported by NASA (NX13ANN34G, NNX15AB45G) and NIH (P20-GM103418).

publications.title: Effects of skeletal unloading on the antibody repertoire of tetanus toxoid and/or CpG treated C57BL/6J mice.
publications.summary: Effects of skeletal unloading on the antibody repertoire of tetanus toxoid and/or CpG treated C57BL/6J mice. — 10.1371/journal.pone.0210284
